geneVariantDescriptions.description: KRAS G12D is a hotspot mutation that lies within a GTP-binding region of the Kras protein (UniProt.org). G12D results in decreased Kras GTPase activity and increased activation of downstream signaling, promotes tumor formation in mouse models (PMID: 16474405, PMID: 26037647, PMID: 22871572), and is transforming in cell culture (PMID: 29533785).

references.title: Biochemical and Structural Analysis of Common Cancer-Associated KRAS Mutations.
